    "28 We have so far only been focusing on the moral evaluation of a single action.",
    "But in ethical decision problems of the real world, it is possible to perform multiple actions.",
    "However, as illustrated in the salad example, the possibility of combining actions can present tractability issues that are inherent to permutations of combinatorial structures.",
    "To show how this affects the computational complexity of consequentialism, 29 we define an action plan = {a 1, a 2, …, a n } as a distinct non-empty set of n actions presented by the environment such that 𝜑 ⊆ E.",
